       <div class="details">
        <p class="head"><span class="info"><a href="#comment-40512">#11</a> written by

           		   <a  id="commentauthor-40512" href="http://www.nytimes.com/"> tarobomb</a>
		   September 19th, 2013 at 20:18</span></p>
               <div class="text">
								<div id="commentbody-40512"> <p>From a bit of trial and error, it looks like the WebSQL limit is actually still 50 MB. You can’t request 50 MB in your initial call to openDatabase—that throws an error—but if you ask for 5 MB or less, you’ll get your database, and it’ll still grow up to 50 MB through a series of user prompts (5, 10, 25 MB) as you insert data.</p>
<p>I have no idea whether this is the intended behavior.</p>
 </div>
               </div>
       </div>
