               <div class="text">
								<div id="commentbody-40528"> <p>Regarding Marek&#8217;s comment about height… if you go here:</p>
<p><a href="http://responsejs.com/labs/dimensions/" rel="nofollow">http://responsejs.com/labs/dimensions/</a></p>
<p>on an iOS 7 iPad, if you look at any of the height methods &#8211; only innerHeight returns the correct height of the browser when the iPad is in landscape mode. Portrait mode works as expected. What is worse, from what I can tell with a &#8220;fullscreen&#8221; web app I have, is that a height=&#8221;100%&#8221; on html, body produces a container 20px too high in landscape mode.</p>
 </div>
