               <div class="text">
								<div id="commentbody-40635"> <p><q><br />
Following Google Chrome, now Safari on iOS doesn’t support the datetime input type anymore and it will fallback to text. This type was deprecated in the standard in favor of using two inputs, date and time for the same purpose.<br />
</q><br />
According to which standard is datetime deprecated? I still find it in the current HTML5 spec by W3C and the WhatWG document. Strange: datetime-local is still supported by both Chrome and Safari 7.</p>
