       <div class="details">
        <p class="head"><span class="info"><a href="#comment-41537">#22</a> written by

                        <b  id="commentauthor-41537">y_ich</b>
		   September 25th, 2013 at 09:34</span></p>
               <div class="text">
								<div id="commentbody-41537"> <p>Thank you for your valuable information.<br />
About home-screen apps, I found 3 things below.<br />
1. watchPosition bug in iOS 6 seems to be solved.<br />
    In iOS 6, there was a bug that callback of navigator.geolocation.watchPosition calls just once, no following consecutive calls.<br />
2, The bug of Web Audio is still in iOS 7.<br />
   There is a bug that outputting a sound by Web Audio cause both home button and power button to be no response in high possibility. iOS 7 has this bug, too.<br />
3. Nitro is now available.<br />
   Home-screen apps&#8217; performance is almost same as Safari&#8217;s.</p>
 </div>
               </div>
       </div>
